# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Pages automatically serves /foo.html at /foo and 308-redirects /foo.html -> /foo.
# Canonicals across the site are therefore extensionless; we only need to handle
# trailing-slash variants and legacy aliases here.
#
# Note: apex -> www (funcitygamesnwa.com -> www.funcitygamesnwa.com) cannot be
# configured here — _redirects sources are path-only. Configure that as a
# Cloudflare Redirect Rule at the zone level (dashboard > Rules > Redirect Rules).

# Trailing-slash variants -> canonical extensionless URL
/about/        /about        301
/contact/      /contact      301
/games/        /games        301
/how-it-works/ /how-it-works 301
/locations/    /locations    301
/venues/       /venues       301

# Legacy/convenience aliases
/home /         301

# Tooling/source files that ship via the Git Integration deploy (.cfignore is
# only honored by `wrangler pages deploy`, not Git pushes). Bounce them home
# with a 302 — Pages _redirects only supports 301/302/303/307/308 status codes
# (4xx rewrites are silently ignored), so a redirect to / is the lightweight
# alternative to wiring up a Pages Function. 302 (not 301) so browsers and
# Google don't cache the mapping permanently in case any of these paths is
# ever legitimately needed later.
/CLAUDE.md                       /  302
/README.md                       /  302
/Makefile                        /  302
/serve.py                        /  302
/.cfignore                       /  302
/.gitignore                      /  302
/.mcp.json                       /  302
/.playwright-mcp.config.json     /  302
/.playwright-mcp/*               /  302
/.vscode/*                       /  302
/.claude/*                       /  302
/.devcontainer/*                 /  302
/.git/*                          /  302
/images/README.md                /  302
